      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "> @wuchiachih the decoding of a raw transaction is currently done based on some heuristics, c.f. #10481, and doesn't always correctly identify whether it is a segwit transaction or not. So the flag can be used to force it to be decoded as segwit or not if needed. If I were you, I would include the flag only if your sanity check fails - that the TXID is different.\r\n\r\nCool.  Sounds like a solution!",
